ate and species range. (1996) Nature, 382, pp. 765-766; Reiter, P., Global warming and malaria: knowing the horse before hitching the cart. (2008) Malaria Journal, 3 S, pp. 1-9; Robinet, C., Roques, A., Direct impacts of recent climate warming on insect populations. (2010) Integrative Zoology, 5, pp. 132-142; Roos, J., Hopkins, R., Kvarnheden, R., The impact of global warming on plant diseases and insect vectors in Sweden. (2011) European Journal of Plant Pathology, 129, pp. 9-19; Schweiger, O., Settele, J., Kudrna, O., Climate change can cause spatial mismatch of trophically interacting species. (2008) Ecology, 89, pp. 3472-3479; Stireman, J.O., Dyer, L.A., Janzen, D.H., Climatic unpredictability and parasitism of caterpillars: implications of global warming. (2005) Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America, 102, pp. 17384-17387; Tauber, M.J., Tauber, C.A., Masaki, S., (1986) Seasonal Adaptations of Insects., , Oxford University Press, New York, New York","Harada, T.; Laboratory of Environmental Physiology, Graduate School of Integrated Sciences of Human and Nature, Kochi University, Kochi 780-8520, Japan; email: haratets@kochi-u.ac.jp",,,,,,,,03076962,,PENTD,,"English","Physiol.Entomol.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-80655148934
